title: For Sale:  Ammo: Speer Gold Dot 9mm 124gr - 50 Round Boxes
postcontent:
Hi. I have several 50 round (not 20 round) boxes of Speer Gold Dot 9mm 124gr JHP, new in the box. These are the best 9mm self-defense hollow point rounds available and even used by law enforcement. They are highly rated. Again, these are FIFTY (50) round boxes, people. The going price for JUST the twenty (20) round box at Gander Mountain and Vance (which are sold out) is $27.99/box + tax (total is $29.87 at 1.0675% tax). If you do the math, that breaks down to $29.87/20= 1.49 per single round. Therefore, a 50-round box at the same price (which they don't sell in town at all) would normally be $1.49ea x 50 rounds = $74.69 per 50 round box.

Using that logic, I propose a very fair price of just $50.00 per 50-round box (only $1.00/round). I consider this to be fair and not price-gouging by any means. (which I have noticed recently here on this website). Hope this helps.

I'm in the north columbus area (Polaris/Westerville/New Albany etc) and any buyer(s) would need to meet me in this general area (21 and over only). Don't ask me if I still have some; if the ad is listed, then they are available. Price is firm. Face to face only; I will not ship them. Thanks.

location: Rocky Mount, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
Browning X-Bolt Composite stalker 270 Winchester. Product Description All business, no nonsense. The X-Bolt stalker isn't flashy, but it is durable, accurate, simple, and has all the elegant lines and curves you'll find on its "prettier" siblings. More and more hunters are turning to the Composite firearms for many reasons. Probably the biggest is that they no longer want to bang up that pretty Walnut stock. The X-Bolt Composite Stalker is an excellent rifle choice for deer hunting in conditions where a hunter may not wish to take the traditional Walnut stocked rifle. The X-Bolt Composite Stalker's stock is made from tough, Composite material that can take a beating. Don't think it would be slippery, unattractive or uncomfortable to fire. The stock is textured for a secure grip from forearm to pistol grip. It also has a comfortable palm-swell and a Dura-Touch Armor Coating over a flat, black finish. The barrel, bolt and receiver are also finished in a flat, durable non-glare surface. This is a rifle with all the deluxe features of the X-Bolt family, but rugged enough for the demanding hard core deer, elk and sheep hunters. • Button-rifled barrel is triple checked for quality and individually hand chambered and air gauged to ensure consistency and accuracy. • The target Crown enables the uniform release of gas as the bullet exits the barrel, preventing a shift in trajectory. The Crown is recessed to protect it from accidental damage that degrades accuracy. • Free floated barrel eliminates contact interference from the fore-end, enabling the superior barrel craftsmanship to perform consistently and accurately. • Drilled and tapped for X-Lock scope mounts that use four screws for each base to provide a rock solid optic platform. • Adjustable Feather Trigger minimizes the "human factor" by eliminating creep and take-up — providing a crisp trigger pull that "breaks like glass." • Low profile action allows you to mount the scope extremely close to the center of the bore to minimize the offset between point of aim and Point of Impact. • 60° bolt lift keeps the thumb and fingers clear of the scope when cycling the action and allows the bolt to be operated in a smoother/quicker motion. • Top-tang safety offers easy accessibility without removing your firing hand from the stock. The shooter can quickly manipulate the safety, or verify the position of the safety, without losing your sight picture or cheek weld. • Detachable Rotary magazine is built from tough polymer and is designed to stop forward movement of the cartridge by contacting the shoulder of the case rather than the tip of the projectile. This prevents bullet tip deformation and recoil induced bullet seating depth change. •Bolt Unlock Button allows the bolt to be cycled with the safety engaged. • Innovative Inflex Technology recoil pad uses directional deflection to pull the stock down and away from the face to reduce perceived recoil. • Durable low-luster blued finish reduces reflective glare •Dura-Touch Armor Coating provides positive gripping surface that is both comfortable and easy to hold onto during all weather conditions.

title: For Sale/Trade:  For all firearms traders/ sellers
location: north carolina, North Carolina, United States
postcontent:
Hey all,
While I understand you want to get the most you can for what you have keep in mind that this is not gun broker. If you want the full cash value of your weapon I suggest you go there. If you buy a weapon for $1000.00 and take it home, you have just lost value because very few people will pay an individual retail especially when they cannot return said item. Most people on here have run of the mill weapons. If you come on here with a gold plated 1911 with all the bells and whistles and say you want to trade, then don't be a dick when someone contacts you with a couple lower end guns. That kind of trade is what this site is about. Granted you may very well trade your gold plated $10,000 pistol for a platinum plated grenade launcher. But what fun is a weapon you are never gonna use.

FOOD FOR THOUGHT, HATE MAIL NOT REQUIRED

title: For Sale/Trade:  1997 Tahoe LT 4x4 4 Door
postcontent:
1997 Tahoe LT (Leather, cruise control, power everything) 4 door in dark green. It is the 5.7L V8 with push button 4x4. It has 156,5*** miles, which is nothing for these engines. They are well known to last over 325,000 miles. It is a suitable family vehicle with "off-road" mods that make it perfect for the hunting land (the reason I bought it initially until my truck was totaled and this has been my daily driver).

It has:
Newer transmission
Newer A/C and (A/C and Heat work great)
Tinted windows
New window shades
Offroad Tires (Buckshot Mudder XMT) (60% tread left)
Offroad Wheels
Small lift with leveling kit
New rear end with U-joints etc.
New high output headlights (white)
New K/C Daylighter fog lights (155 watt per light) with a dash switch with light
Fresh oil and fluid change
New windshield wipers (Bosch)
Leather seats, console, etc.
Tilt wheel
Cruise control
Power everything
CD player and updated sound system with Kicker 10" subwoofer and amp
Tape to MP3 Converter (Plays Mp3 player or Ipod through the stereo)
Compass in rearview mirror

The only "bad" things with the Tahoe is a tear in driver's seat (~$60 fix), a dent in the tailgate, and the clear coat on the paint is fading on the hood and roof (it is not terrible and it is very common on these vehicles).

Mechanically, this truck is perfect. No "check engine" lights or anything. I drive it everyday and it is 100% dependable and will take you anywhere you could possibly want to go. It was not abused or taken "Off-Roading". The 4x4 works great, i tried it just to see if it works, but it is never used. The reason I am selling is because it is just me and my wife and we both have big 4x4 SUVs since she got one for Christmas. So, I am ready for another sports car around the same price range as the Tahoe.

title: For Sale:  M1903 Excellent Condition PRICE LOWERED
postcontent:
Offered is my M1903A3 rifle in Excellent Condition made by Remington. I believe this rifle was a factory rebuild as the barrel is stamped 12-43 and it has the later pistol grip stock. I don't think it was ever issued after the rebuild. It is in great shape, blueing is outstanding, the wood is very nice and has no significant imperfections, action operates smoothly and the trigger is very nice; everything about this rifle is correct and I can find nothing out of place or incorrect about it. I bought this rifle in 1987 when the Firearms Protection Act of 1986 allowed the importation of surplus military rifles into our country again. This rifle is from the first batch of imports from that era and these early imports were hand picked and were the best of the bunch.  When I got this rifle I removed the cosmoline and brown storage paper this rifle came packed in, wiped it down, and fired 20 rds of non corrosive ammo thru it for a functions check, everything worked as it should and it shot a very tight respectable group. I then cleaned the bore, applied a light coat of oil to everything, then put it into my climatically controlled vault where it has sat largely untouched since. This rifle is complete, fully intact, fully function, shoots to point of aim and has not been modified, restored, or altered in anyway from its original configuration. The bore has no pitting or rust that I can see with a bore light and the rifling is excellent; the lands and grooves and sharp and crisp.  You will not be disappointed with this rifle. I am retiring and have too many guns than I can take with me when I move so I am selling the last and best of my military rifle collection. I will meet buyer between Charlotte Hall and Upper Marlboro for a FTF cash and carry deal during daylight hours in a public setting. This sale has no tax, no shipping or transfer fees, no paper work, no govt registration, and it is available now, and this transaction is 100% legal in the state of Maryland. Buyer must be a MD resident who is not prohibited by law from owning firearms or active duty military living in MD. Not interested in trades of any sort, pls do not contact me if you are prohibited from owning firearms or for any kind of strawman sale. thanks for looking, pls email with any questions.

Up for sale is an Arc Teryx Blade 24 laptop backpack. Barely used condition. Fabric, zippers, straps are all in perfect condition. The backpack has two main compartments; one narrow that fits a 15" laptop and one larger outside pocket.
